The interval $[-17,17]$ has length 34, and the intervals $[-17,0)$ and $(5,17]$ have total length 27.  Therefore, the probability that the equation has at least two distinct real roots is $\frac{27}{34}$, and $m + n = 27 + 34 = \boxed{61}$.
